Let's pick bamboo grass.

24
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:23,882
Big brother!

25
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:29,429
I want to pick bamboo grass.

26
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,603
You promised to go with me.

27
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:37,979
I've got homework.

28
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,196
That's not homework.

29
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:47,739
It's an English magazine.

30
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,744
What a stupid moustache.

31
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:55,789
He's a famous Italian aircraft designer.

32
00:06:56,092 --> 00:06:58,344
His name is Caproni.

33
00:06:58,364 --> 00:07:00,616
It says he's a count.

34
00:07:00,805 --> 00:07:02,348
- Your face is scratched.

35
00:07:02,368 --> 00:07:03,911
- Leave it alone.

36
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:06,758
I better put some iodine on it.

37
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:08,802
Would you be quiet?

38
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:21,982
Big brother, what are you doing?

39
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:23,817
You're not allowed up here.

40
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,485
You're not wearing glasses.

41
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:29,990
Focusing on the stars should improve my eyesight.

42
00:07:31,669 --> 00:07:33,150
- Mother will scold you.

43
00:07:33,170 --> 00:07:34,651
- A shooting star!

44
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,747
There's another one.

45
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:40,102
They're pretty.

46
00:07:40,122 --> 00:07:41,214
See?

47
00:07:41,234 --> 00:07:42,326
Like that.

48
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:45,839
There's so many of them.

49
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:25,045
I'm a Japanese boy.

50
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:33,345
I think this is my dream.

51
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:52,405
This is my dream, you know.

52
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:54,324
It's mine too.

53
00:08:54,533 --> 00:08:55,909
Your dream?

54
00:08:56,087 --> 00:08:58,319
Listen, Japanese boy.

55
00:08:58,339 --> 00:09:00,571
You think we are sharing this dream?

56
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:01,915
It's strange.

57
00:09:02,093 --> 00:09:04,241
You're Count Caproni, aren't you?

58
00:09:04,261 --> 00:09:06,409
I'm very glad to meet you.

59
00:09:07,765 --> 00:09:09,191
Interesting.

60
00:09:09,211 --> 00:09:10,637
Yes, this is a dream.

61
00:09:10,657 --> 00:09:12,083
This world is a dream.

62
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:14,094
Welcome to my kingdom.

63
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,762
I'm honored.

64
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,765
Look at them.

65
00:09:24,031 --> 00:09:26,013
They will bomb the enemy city.

66
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,015
Most of them won't return.

67
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,284
But the war will soon be over.

68
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,128
Climb up, Japanese boy.

69
00:09:50,099 --> 00:09:52,456
This is my dream.

70
00:09:52,476 --> 00:09:54,833
When the war is over, I will build this.

71
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,763
Magnificent, isn't she?

72
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:00,807
Let's fly.

73
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:07,564
Instead of bombs, she'll carry passengers.

74
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,492
Of course we can't climb up here...

75
00:10:19,712 --> 00:10:21,172
but dreams are convenient.

76
00:10:21,192 --> 00:10:22,652
One can go anywhere.

77
00:10:30,264 --> 00:10:32,058
Come, join me.

78
00:10:32,078 --> 00:10:33,872
You can walk along the spar.

79
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,180
Take a look.

80
00:11:15,393 --> 00:11:17,291
- She's beautiful, no?

81
00:11:17,311 --> 00:11:19,209
- Yes, incredible.

82
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:27,477
She'll carry a hundred people across the Atlantic.

83
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:30,220
Mr.

84
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:30,970
Caproni?

85
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:31,720
I have a question.

86
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:36,236
Do you think I could design airplanes?

87
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:40,188
I'll never be a pilot.

88
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:41,730
I'm too nearsighted.

89
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:45,412
Listen, Japanese boy.

90
00:11:45,631 --> 00:11:47,258
I'm not a pilot.

91
00:11:47,278 --> 00:11:48,905
I don't even know how to fly.

92
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:52,919
To fly airplanes is simple.

93
00:11:53,347 --> 00:11:55,495
But I am a creator of airplanes.

94
00:11:55,515 --> 00:11:57,663
An aeronautical engineer!

95
00:11:58,217 --> 00:11:59,217
Yes!

96
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:01,594
Listen to me, Japanese boy.

97
00:12:01,814 --> 00:12:03,941
Airplanes are not tools for war.

98
00:12:03,961 --> 00:12:06,088
They are not for making money.

99
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:08,768
Airplanes are beautiful dreams.

100
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:12,063
Engineers turn dreams into reality.

101
00:12:12,606 --> 00:12:13,565
Yes!

102
00:12:13,868 --> 00:12:15,265
Arrivederci.

103
00:12:15,285 --> 00:12:16,682
We'll meet again.

104
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:33,960
Jiro, you should go to bed.

105
00:12:35,139 --> 00:12:37,454
You startled me.

106
00:12:37,474 --> 00:12:39,789
I heard you talking to someone.

107
00:12:40,634 --> 00:12:43,303
Mother, I'm going to be an aeronautical engineer.

108
00:12:43,481 --> 00:12:44,878
Really?

109
00:12:44,898 --> 00:12:46,295
That's a wonderful dream.

110
00:12:46,775 --> 00:12:48,402
Airplanes are beautiful dreams.

111
00:12:48,422 --> 00:12:50,049
That's what he told me.

112
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:52,604
I want to design beautiful airplanes.

113
00:13:21,727 --> 00:13:22,832
You, there.

114
00:13:22,852 --> 00:13:23,957
Come, take my seat.

115
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,178
Pardon me.

116
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:26,429
Please.

117
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:04,717
The wind feels wonderful.

118
